verbose_text: The role of isoflavones in increasing bone mineral density is associated with the inhibition of osteoclast activity, activation of osteoblasts, and elevated concentration of insulin like growth factor I (IGF-I), which stimulates synthesis of collagen and secretion of parathormone, and increases blood concentration of calcium [XREF_BIBR, XREF_BIBR, XREF_BIBR, XREF_BIBR].
evidence: insulin-like growth factor I (IGF-I), which stimulates synthesis of collagen and secretion of parathormone
